To calculate the percentage increase in GDP from 2018 to 2022, we can use the following formula:

Percentage Increase = ((New Value - Old Value) / Old Value) \* 100%

In this case, the old value is the GDP in 2018, which was $1.547 trillion, and the new value is the GDP in 2022, which was $2.0 trillion. Plugging these values into the formula, we get:

Percentage Increase = (($2.0 trillion - $1.547 trillion) / $1.547 trillion) \* 100%

Percentage Increase = (($453 billion) / $1.547 trillion) \* 100%

Percentage Increase = 0.292 \* 100%

Percentage Increase = 29.2%

So, the percentage increase in New York (state)'s GDP from 2018 to 2022 was approximately 29.2%.
